cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a computationally efficient approach to detecting objects in 3D point clouds using convolutional neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a novel approach to processing 3D data. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of L1 regularization, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL).
